# Commit message format:
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# Type: feat, fix, docs, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, style
# Scope: main.cpp, FingerPrint_Enroll.ino, serialport, cmake, docs, etc.
# Subject: imperative mood, lowercase, no period
#
# CHANGELOG ENTRY (if releasing):
# Version: (e.g., 0.10.0 or 1.0.1)
# Section: Added, Changed, Fixed, Removed, Deprecated, Security
# Entry: Brief description of user-facing change
#
# Example:
# feat(main.cpp): add status code validation
#
# Version: 0.5.1
# Section: Fixed
# Entry: - Status code validation prevents invalid responses from crashing host app
#
